the best Store listing,

00:11:16.130 --> 00:11:17.430
we need to experiment.

00:11:17.430 --> 00:11:19.440
This is where Store Listing
Experiments come in.

00:11:19.440 --> 00:11:21.620
This feature has been
a very big success

00:11:21.620 --> 00:11:23.470
with developers
in the past year.

00:11:23.470 --> 00:11:25.960
More than 70% of
our top developers

00:11:25.960 --> 00:11:28.245
are using the feature.

00:11:28.245 --> 00:11:30.370
We often get feedback from
developers, for example,

00:11:30.370 --> 00:11:32.480
like this one from
Goodgame Studios,

00:11:32.480 --> 00:11:34.930
that it drives significant
uplift to their conversion

00:11:34.930 --> 00:11:36.555
rate.

00:11:36.555 --> 00:11:38.689
KOBI GLICK: A big opportunity
to get more installs

00:11:38.689 --> 00:11:40.980
is optimizing the top of the
funnel, your Store listing

00:11:40.980 --> 00:11:41.860
page.

00:11:41.860 --> 00:11:43.960
This is where users make
their install decision,

00:11:43.960 --> 00:11:46.260
regardless of whether they
found the app through Search

00:11:46.260 --> 00:11:48.180
or via a deep link.

00:11:48.180 --> 00:11:50.680
Before we launched it, you had
to use a bunch of workarounds

00:11:50.680 --> 00:11:51.570
and spend some budget.

00:11:51.570 --> 00:11:53.028
You can see the
feedback from Rovio

00:11:53.028 --> 00:11:54.810
here on how they had
to run icon tests.

00:11:54.810 --> 00:11:55.911
They spent budget.

00:11:55.911 --> 00:11:57.910
After we launched it, you
can see their feedback

00:11:57.910 --> 00:12:00.520
about soft launching
first on Google Play

00:12:00.520 --> 00:12:03.258
as it allows them to better
understand their users.

00:12:07.596 --> 00:12:09.970
Store Listing Experiments have
been seeing great success.

00:12:09.970 --> 00:12:12.060
In the last year, you can
see Flaregames up here,

00:12:12.060 --> 00:12:14.220
30% increase in installs.

00:12:14.220 --> 00:12:16.980
ERepublik Labs, running
this exactly the way we

00:12:16.980 --> 00:12:19.730
thought about it, as a rapid
iteration and experimentation

00:12:19.730 --> 00:12:20.540
tool.

00:12:20.540 --> 00:12:23.650
Expedia, 10% increase
of installs globally.

00:12:23.650 --> 00:12:25.580
And actually, their
most successful test

00:12:25.580 --> 00:12:27.010
was reordering screenshots.

00:12:29.267 --> 00:12:31.100
MILENA NIKOLIC: Here
are some best practices

00:12:31.100 --> 00:12:33.530
when running Store
Listening Experiments.

00:12:33.530 --> 00:12:36.530
Create a hypothesis first.

00:12:36.530 --> 00:12:39.430
Make sure you know what
you're trying to prove.

00:12:39.430 --> 00:12:42.500
Next, test one thing at a time.

00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:45.050
Run your experiments
until they have reached

00:12:45.050 --> 00:12:46.400
statistical significance.

00:12:46.400 --> 00:12:48.510
We'll let you know
when this has happened.

00:12:48.510 --> 00:12:50.940
Minor tweaks often
have minor impact.

00:12:50.940 --> 00:12:52.610
Consider bold
changes, especially

00:12:52.610 --> 00:12:54.780
if you're early in
your startup's life.

00:12:54.780 --> 00:12:56.180
And finally, keep testing.

00:12:56.180 --> 00:12:59.874
The next major improvement
may be still to come.

00:12:59.874 --> 00:13:02.290
Here is some great feedback
we received from Jamie Berger,

00:13:02.290 --> 00:13:04.180
head of marketing at Scopely.

00:13:04.180 --> 00:13:06.290
We can see how this
feature encourages

00:13:06.290 --> 00:13:09.800
testing and validation
of new and bold ideas.

00:13:09.800 --> 00:13:12.410
We were very happy to
see how they used this

00:13:12.410 --> 00:13:16.160
as their go-to tool for market
testing and optimization.

00:13:16.160 --> 00:13:18.540
KOBI GLICK: OK, so here's
some great examples

00:13:18.540 --> 00:13:21.670
of the best practices in
action with Instacart.

00:13:21.670 --> 00:13:23.910
We've learned that an
app description that

00:13:23.910 --> 00:13:27.370
clearly shows your app value
to users just works better.

00:13:27.370 --> 00:13:29.840
So you can see control
versus experiment.

00:13:29.840 --> 00:13:31.750
Experiment is much clearer.

00:13:31.750 --> 00:13:35.230
Plus 14% in installs.

00:13:35.230 --> 00:13:36.940
And here's a bunch
of great examples

00:13:36.940 --> 00:13:38.340
from Concrete Software.

00:13:38.340 --> 00:13:40.220
Sometimes, you just get lucky.

00:13:40.220 --> 00:13:43.760
They run an icon test for
"NHL Hockey Target Smash."

00:13:43.760 --> 00:13:46.160
Plus 70% installs.

00:13:46.160 --> 00:13:46.930
Boom.

00:13:46.930 --> 00:13:47.970
It's great, right?

00:13:47.970 --> 00:13:50.380
But sometimes, you actually
need to launch, iterate,

00:13:50.380 --> 00:13:51.929
and experiment a lot.

00:13:51.929 --> 00:13:53.470
So with "PBA Bowling
Challenge," they

00:13:53.470 --> 00:13:56.310
ran a series of experiments,
and every icon that you see here

00:13:56.310 --> 00:13:59.640
represents a complete
series of experiments.

00:13:59.640 --> 00:14:03.020
They also iterated on their
description, screenshots,

00:14:03.020 --> 00:14:07.220
and their order, leading to
a compound effect of 63%.

00:14:07.220 --> 00:14:10.080
This is incredible.

00:14:10.080 --> 00:14:12.670
Now, let's see an example from
mixi, a leading game developer

00:14:12.670 --> 00:14:14.850
from Japan, that will
show us how a leading game

00:14:14.850 --> 00:14:16.580
developer thinks
about localization

00:14:16.580 --> 00:14:18.170
and experimentation.

00:14:18.170 --> 00:14:20.245
When mixi wanted to take
their big hit "Monster

00:14:20.245 --> 00:14:23.750
Strike" to the US, they ran
a series of experiments.

00:14:23.750 --> 00:14:26.490
They tested the icon, the
screenshots, the description,

00:14:26.490 --> 00:14:28.840
and the video.

00:14:28.840 --> 00:14:31.380
In this chart, you can see
how they ran the experiments

00:14:31.380 --> 00:14:34.710
methodically and scientifically,
leading to a compound effect

00:14:34.710 --> 00:14:37.910
of 68% in installs.

00:14:37.910 --> 00:14:39.630
Start Listing
Experiments helped mixi

00:14:39.630 --> 00:14:42.370
understand the difference
in taste and flavor

00:14:42.370 --> 00:14:45.080
between users in the
US and users in Japan

00:14:45.080 --> 00:14:49.690
and help them localized
their games much better.

00:14:49.690 --> 00:14:52.870
And here's the feedback we got
