AARON ROTHMAN: Anyways,
anyways, I promise no more.

00:23:41.385 --> 00:23:42.760
So this is where
we want to start

00:23:42.760 --> 00:23:44.130
with building something great.

00:23:47.450 --> 00:23:55.020
So based on some
internal analysis,

00:23:55.020 --> 00:23:58.000
we found that permissions,
footprint, and design

00:23:58.000 --> 00:24:00.700
were all key components
when it came to a user's

00:24:00.700 --> 00:24:04.730
perception of a great app.

00:24:04.730 --> 00:24:06.400
So starting with permissions.

00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:08.080
Excessive permissions
can actually

00:24:08.080 --> 00:24:11.092
deter a user from installing
your app in the first place.

00:24:11.092 --> 00:24:12.800
It's important to
remember-- if you don't

00:24:12.800 --> 00:24:16.940
need it, don't ask for it.

00:24:16.940 --> 00:24:18.800
Users may be wary
of installing apps

00:24:18.800 --> 00:24:21.260
where the permissions don't
seem to align with the app

00:24:21.260 --> 00:24:22.500
functionality.

00:24:22.500 --> 00:24:24.840
For example, why
does a child's game

00:24:24.840 --> 00:24:29.080
need to access my
phone's call logs?

00:24:29.080 --> 00:24:31.020
Second is footprint.

00:24:31.020 --> 00:24:34.360
Some users may be scared off
by the footprint of your app.

00:24:34.360 --> 00:24:36.660
These users may be on
poor internet connections

00:24:36.660 --> 00:24:38.680
or have limited phone memory.

00:24:38.680 --> 00:24:41.720
This is especially true
in emerging markets,

00:24:41.720 --> 00:24:45.730
where there are both phone
and network limitations.

00:24:45.730 --> 00:24:50.070
So it's helpful to be mindful
of SDK compatibility, APK

00:24:50.070 --> 00:24:52.550
size, and memory usage.

00:24:52.550 --> 00:24:54.480
Sometimes, less is more.

00:24:58.040 --> 00:24:59.510
Third is design.

00:24:59.510 --> 00:25:01.960
So the users installed your app.

00:25:01.960 --> 00:25:04.360
Now, you want to ensure
a great experience.

00:25:04.360 --> 00:25:07.710
So remember to limit
the cognitive load.

00:25:07.710 --> 00:25:10.820
A well-designed app is
intuitive and consistent

00:25:10.820 --> 00:25:13.050
and does not require
a user to hunt,

00:25:13.050 --> 00:25:15.760
guess, remember,
or otherwise strain

00:25:15.760 --> 00:25:17.330
their brains trying
to figure out

00:25:17.330 --> 00:25:19.420
how to interact with your app.

00:25:19.420 --> 00:25:22.350
One tangible solution for
making a highly usable app

00:25:22.350 --> 00:25:27.960
is implementing Google's design
spec, known as material design.

00:25:27.960 --> 00:25:31.550
Here are two examples of apps
that invested more in quality

00:25:31.550 --> 00:25:34.140
by adopting material
design, which

00:25:34.140 --> 00:25:37.390
led to the benefit of
more user engagement.

00:25:37.390 --> 00:25:39.040
It's pretty impressive,
for example,

00:25:39.040 --> 00:25:43.800
that Trello saw a 41% increase
in activity per session

00:25:43.800 --> 00:25:45.195
by implementing material design.

00:25:48.710 --> 00:25:52.300
So you can do your best
to build a great app.

00:25:52.300 --> 00:25:55.850
But how can you be sure
it's actually great?

00:25:55.850 --> 00:25:59.580
More than half of poor user
reviews are quality related,

00:25:59.580 --> 00:26:03.830
and a third of those are
just about bugs and crashes.

00:26:03.830 --> 00:26:07.160
It can be difficult to get it
right in the first iteration.

00:26:07.160 --> 00:26:09.480
So we recommend following
the earlier advice of Milena

00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:13.520
and Kobi and using beta
testing and staged rollouts

00:26:13.520 --> 00:26:16.566
to ensure that your app
is great when it launches.

00:26:20.720 --> 00:26:23.660
So we've covered building
and launching a great app.

00:26:23.660 --> 00:26:25.740
Now, just because
your app is launched,

00:26:25.740 --> 00:26:29.450
it doesn't mean you need to
stop engaging with your users.

00:26:29.450 --> 00:26:31.880
Listening to your users
is important for continued

00:26:31.880 --> 00:26:34.250
success, and I'm
going to explain why.

00:26:37.070 --> 00:26:39.530
You have a unique
opportunity in Android

00:26:39.530 --> 00:26:41.690
to engage with
your users directly

00:26:41.690 --> 00:26:45.300
by replying to the reviews
via the Developer Console

00:26:45.300 --> 00:26:51.040
and building an even more
loved app as a result.

00:26:51.040 --> 00:26:53.760
One example is Aviary,
who created a dialogue

00:26:53.760 --> 00:26:56.800
with their users by
engaging with feedback.

00:26:56.800 --> 00:27:00.330
This responsiveness
led to 50% of reviewers

00:27:00.330 --> 00:27:02.460
revising their scores higher.

00:27:02.460 --> 00:27:03.680
It's crazy, right?

00:27:03.680 --> 00:27:05.860
User feedback can help
make your app better,

00:27:05.860 --> 00:27:08.020
leading to higher
ratings and a boost

00:27:08.020 --> 00:27:09.255
in discovery opportunities.

00:27:13.482 --> 00:27:15.440
LARISSA FONTAINE: So
after building a great app

00:27:15.440 --> 00:27:17.100
and listening to
your users, it's

00:27:17.100 --> 00:27:19.340
important to create a
Play Store listing that

00:27:19.340 --> 00:27:23.982
quickly and accurately reflects
what your app is about.

00:27:23.982 --> 00:27:25.940
You're all familiar with
the different elements

00:27:25.940 --> 00:27:26.910
of your listing.

00:27:26.910 --> 00:27:30.320
These really require some
thoughtful attention.

00:27:30.320 --> 00:27:31.830
We've provided
multiple ways for you

00:27:31.830 --> 00:27:34.840
to communicate the value of
your app, and it's up to you

00:27:34.840 --> 00:27:37.610
to ensure they capture the
most important and interesting

00:27:37.610 --> 00:27:39.940
information.

00:27:39.940 --> 00:27:43.010
And each of them, from the
title to the description

00:27:43.010 --> 00:27:45.280
to the images,
provide metadata that

00:27:45.280 --> 00:27:48.030
help us understand
what your app does

00:27:48.030 --> 00:27:51.720
and who's most likely to use it.

00:27:51.720 --> 00:27:55.760
It sounds easy, but no one
gets it right the first time.

00:27:55.760 --> 00:27:59.380
And this is why we created Store
Listing Experiments to help you

00:27:59.380 --> 00:28:01.520
refine each of these elements.

